y/go-ontology/issues/31730\" xsd:anyURI\n\n[Term]\nid: GO:0050353\nname: trimethyllysine dioxygenase activity\nnamespace: molecular_function\ndef: \"Catalysis of the reaction: 2-oxoglutarate + N(6),N(6),N(6)-trimethyl-L-lysine + O2 = 3-hydroxy-N(6),N(6),N(6)-trimethyl-L-lysine + CO2 + succinate.\" [EC:1.14.11.8, RHEA:14181]\nsynonym: \"6-N,6-N,6-N-trimethyl-L-lysine,2-oxoglutarate:oxygen oxidoreductase (3-hydroxylating)\" RELATED [EC:1.14.11.8]\nsynonym: \"epsilon-trimethyllysine 2-oxoglutarate dioxygenase activity\" RELATED [EC:1.14.11.8]\nsynonym: \"N6,N6,N6-trimethyl-L-lysine,2-oxoglutarate:oxygen oxidoreductase (3-hydroxylating)\" RELATED [EC:1.14.11.8]\nsynonym: \"TML dioxygenase activity\" RELATED [EC:1.14.11.8]\nsynonym: \"TML hydroxylase activity\" RELATED [EC:1.14.11.8]\nsynonym: \"TML-alpha-ketoglutarate dioxygenase activity\" RELATED [EC:1.14.11.8]\nsynonym: \"TMLD activity\" RELATED [EC:1.14.11.8]\nsynonym: \"trimethyllysine alpha-ketoglutarate dioxygenase activity\" RELATED [EC:1.14.11.8]\nsynonym: \"trimethyllysine,2-oxoglutarate dioxygenase activity\" RELATED [EC:1.14.11.8]\nxref: EC:1.14.11.8 {source=\"skos:exactMatch\"}\nxref: KEGG_REACTION:R03451\nxref: MetaCyc:TRIMETHYLLYSINE-DIOXYGENASE-RXN\nxref: RHEA:14181 {source=\"skos:exactMatch\"}\nis_a: GO:0016706 ! 2-oxoglutarate-dependent dioxygenase activity\nproperty_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/30193\" xsd:anyURI\n\n[Term]\nid: GO:0050359\nname: obsolete tropomyosin kinase activity\nnamespace: molecular_function\ndef: \"OBSOLETE. Catalysis of the reaction: ATP + tropomyosin = ADP + O-phosphotropomyosin.\" [MetaCyc:TROPOMYOSIN-KINASE-RXN]\ncomment: The reason for obsoletion is that there are no proteins associated with this EC, and this reaction is not found in RHEA.\nsynonym: \"ATP:tropomyosin O-phosphotransferase activity\" RELATED []\nsynonym: \"STK\" RELATED []\nsynonym: \"tropomyosin kinase (phosphorylating) activity\" RELATED []\nproperty_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/29112\" xsd:anyURI\nis_obsolete: true\n\n[Term]\nid: GO:0050367\nname: tyrosine-arginine ligase activity\nnamespace: molecular_function\ndef: \"Catalysis of the reaction: L-arginine + L-tyrosine + ATP = L-tyrosyl-L-arginine + AMP + diphosphate + 2 H+.\" [EC:6.3.2.24, RHEA:15345]\nsynonym: \"kyotorphin synthase activity\" RELATED [EC:6.3.2.24]\nsynonym: \"kyotorphin synthetase activity\" RELATED [EC:6.3.2.24]\nsynonym: \"kyotorphin-synthesizing enzyme activity\" RELATED [EC:6.3.2.24]\nsynonym: \"L-tyrosine:L-arginine ligase (AMP-forming)\" RELATED [EC:6.3.2.24]\nsynonym: \"tyrosyl-arginine synthase activity\" RELATED [EC:6.3.2.24]\nxref: EC:6.3.2.24 {source=\"skos:exactMatch\"}\nxref: KEGG_REACTION:R00735\nxref: MetaCyc:TYROSINE--ARGININE-LIGASE-RXN\nxref: RHEA:15345 {source=\"skos:exactMatch\"}\nis_a: GO:0016881 ! acid-amino acid ligase activity\nproperty_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/30193\" xsd:anyURI\n\n[Term]\nid: GO:0050368\nname: L-tyrosine 2,3-aminomutase activity\nnamespace: molecular_function\ndef: \"Catalysis of the reaction: L-tyrosine = 3-amino-3-(4-hydroxyphenyl)propanoate.\" [RHEA:15781]\nsynonym: \"tyrosine 2,3-aminomutase activity\" RELATED []\nsynonym: \"tyrosine alpha,beta-mutase activity\" RELATED [EC:5.4.3.6]\nxref: EC:5.4.3.6 {source=\"skos:exactMatch\"}\nxref: KEGG_REACTION:R00739\nxref: MetaCyc:TYROSINE-23-AMINOMUTASE-RXN\nxref: RHEA:15781 {source=\"skos:exactMatch\"}\nis_a: GO:0016869 ! intramolecular aminotransferase activity\nproperty_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/30193\" xsd:anyURI\n\n[Term]\nid: GO:0050371\nname: tyrosine phenol-lyase activity\nnamespace: molecular_function\ndef: \"Catalysis of the reaction: L-tyrosine + H2O = NH4 + phenol + pyruvate.\" [EC:4.1.99.2, RHEA:21704]\nsynonym: \"beta-tyrosinase activity\" RELATED [EC:4.1.99.2]\nsynonym: \"L-tyrosine phenol-lyase (deaminating)\" RELATED [EC:4.1.99.2]\nsynonym: \"L-tyrosine phenol-lyase (deaminating; pyruvate-forming)\" RELATED [EC:4.1.99.2]\nxref: EC:4.1.99.2 {source=\"skos:exactMatch\"}\nxref: KEGG_REACTION:R00728\nxref: MetaCyc:TYROSINE-PHENOL-LYASE-RXN\nxref: RHEA:21704 {source=\"skos:exactMatch\"}\nis_a: GO:0016830 ! carbon-carbon lyase activity\nproperty_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/30193\" xsd:anyURI\n\n[Term]\nid: GO:0050477\nname: acyl-lysine deacylase activity\nnamespace: molecular_function\ndef: \"Catalysis of the reaction: H2O + N6-acyl-L-lysine = L-lysine + a carboxylate.\" [EC:3.5.1.17]\nsynonym: \"6-N-acyl-L-lysine amidohydrolase activity\" RELATED [EC:3.5.1.17]\nsynonym: \"epsilon-lysine acylase activity\" RELATED [EC:3.5.1.17]\nsynonym: \"N6-acyl-L-lysine amidohydrolase activity\" RELATED [EC:3.5.1.17]\nxref: EC:3.5.1.17 {source=\"skos:exactMatch\"}\nxref: MetaCyc:ACYL-LYSINE-DEACYLASE-RXN\nxref: RHEA:24548 {source=\"skos:exactMatch\"}\nis_a: GO:0016811 ! hydrolase activity, acting on carbon-nitrogen (but not peptide) bonds, in linear amides\nproperty_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/30193\" xsd:anyURI\n\n[Term]\nid: GO:0090443\nname: FAR/SIN/STRIPAK complex\nnamespace: cellular_component\ndef: \"A conserved protein phosphatase type 2A complex which contains a protein phosphatase type 2A, a protein phosphatase regulatory subunit, a striatin, an FHA domain protein and other subunits (at least six proteins). In fission yeast this complex negatively regulate the septation initiation network at the spindle pole body.\" [GOC:vw, PMID:21561862, PMID:22119525]\nsynonym: \"FAR complex\" RELATED [GOC:vw]\nsynonym: \"SIN inhibitory phosphatase (SIP) complex\" EXACT []\nsynonym: \"SIN inhibitory phosphatase complex\" EXACT []\nsynonym: \"SIP complex\" EXACT [PMID:22119525]\nsynonym: \"striatin interacting phosphatase and kinase complex\" EXACT [GOC:vw]\nsynonym: \"STRIPAK signalling complex\" RELATED [GOC:vw]\nis_a: GO:0032991 ! protein-containing complex\ncreated_by: tb\ncreation_date: 2012-08-23T14:20:39Z\n\n[Term]\nid: GO:0160065\nname: SIN/MEN signaling complex\nnamespace: cellular_component\ndef: \"A protein complex associated with the mitotic spindle pole body during interphase and mitosis and comprises of the proteins of the septation initiation signaling network (SIN) of fission yeast or mitotic exit network (MEN) of budding yeast, organized by two scaffold/adaptor proteins.\" [PMID:21131906, PMID:22525225, PMID:22684255]\nsynonym: \"Hippo signaling complex\" NARROW []\nsynonym: \"MEN signaling complex\" NARROW []\nsynonym: \"SIN signaling complex\" NARROW []\nsynonym: \"SIN/MEN signalling complex\" EXACT []\nis_a: GO:0032991 ! protein-containing complex\nrelationship: part_of GO:0061499 ! outer plaque of mitotic spindle pole body\ncreated_by: rynl\ncreation_date: 2022-11-30T01:39:25Z\n\n[Term]\nid: GO:0160066\nname: interphase SIN signaling complex\nnamespace: cellular_component\ndef: \"A SIN signaling complex associated with the old mitotic spindle pole body during interphase and early M-phase and characterised by the presence active ubiquitin ligase (Dma1 in fission yeast) and GTPase activator (Spg1 in fission yeast) to inactivate SIN signaling.\" [PMID:21131906]\nsynonym: \"interphase SIN signalling complex\" EXACT []\nis_a: GO:0160065 ! SIN/MEN signaling complex\ncreated_by: rynl\ncreation_date: 2022-11-30T03:39:16Z\n\n[Term]\nid: GO:0160067\nname: new spindle pole body SIN signaling complex\nnamespace: cellular_component\ndef: \"A SIN signaling complex associated with the new mitotic spindle pole body during anaphase and characterized by the presence activated (GTP bound) GTPase (Spg1 in fission yeast) to activate SIN signaling.\" [PMID:21131906]\nsynonym: \"new spindle pole body SIN signalling complex\" EXACT []\nis_a: GO:0160065 ! SIN/MEN signaling complex\ncreated_by: rynl\ncreation_date: 2022-11-30T03:42:24Z\n\n[Term]\nid: